description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deputy Human Resources Business Partner - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diagnostic and Therapies Division&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours – Fixed term 12 months &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;**Happy to discuss flexible working opportunities**&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Division of Diagnostics and Therapies is one of five clinical Divisions at University Hospitals Bristol and Weston, comprising eleven diagnostic, therapy and clinical support services with a staffing establishment of approximately 1100 whole-time equivalents, including a high proportion of Allied Health Professionals and Health Care Scientists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This fixed term post is a great development opportunity for an experienced HR practitioner to support the HR Business Partners, Divisional management team and service leads with the delivery of the Divisional workforce objectives within our diagnostic and therapy services. You will be working with managers on complex HR issues, change management and organisation development. Working closely with the (job share) HR Business Partners, you will influence key business decisions to ensure the effective management of staff through the fair, efficient and pragmatic application of best practice. You will have a creative approach to problem solving, a proven track record of supporting staff engagement activities and improving staff experience for a range of staff groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Byrne, HR Business Partner on sarah.byrne@uhbw.nhs.uk or telephone 0117 34 29025&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Philippa Finch, HR Business Partner, by e-mail on Philippa.Finch@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
